  "prompt": "How can I know who views my Instagram profile?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Instagram does not provide a feature that allows users to see who has viewed their profile. However, you can see who has viewed your stories and reels, as this information is visible for 24 hours after posting.\n\nIf you're looking to understand your audience better, you might consider switching to a business or creator account. These accounts provide insights into your posts and audience engagement but still do not show specific profile viewers.\n\nIf you come across any third-party apps that claim to show you who viewed your profile, be cautious, as they may compromise your account security or violate Instagram's terms of service. Always prioritize your privacy and security when using social media platforms.",
